name: src/deletion/delete_case0.js
delete_case0
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is black
  - all root-leaf paths going through n have a black height of b - 1
  - all other root-leaf paths have a black height of b

return.description: The root of the modified subtree.

name: src/deletion/delete_case1.js
delete_case1
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is black
  - all root-leaf paths going through n have a black height of b - 1
  - all other root-leaf paths have a black height of b
  - n is not the root

return.description: The root of the modified subtree.

name: src/deletion/delete_case2.js
delete_case2
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is black
  - all root-leaf paths going through n have a black height of b - 1
  - all other root-leaf paths have a black height of b
  - n is not the root
  - n's sibling is black

return.description: The root of the modified subtree.

name: src/deletion/delete_case5.js
delete_case5
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is black
  - all root-leaf paths going through n have a black height of b - 1
  - all other root-leaf paths have a black height of b
  - n is not the root
  - n's sibling is black
  - if n is a left child, the right child of n's sibling is red
  - if n is a right child, the left child of n's sibling is red

return.description: The root of the modified subtree.

name: src/deletion/delete_no_child.js
delete_no_child
description: Delete a node n that has no non-leaf child. Precondition: - n has no non-leaf child. - n is not the root

return.description: The root of the modified subtree.

name: src/deletion/delete_one_child.js
delete_one_child
description: Delete a node n with one non-leaf left child and one leaf right child. p | n (BLACK) / \ RED - / \ - - Precondition: - n has exactly one non-leaf child. - n is not the root - n's only non-leaf child is n's left child. - hence, n's right child is a leaf - hence, n's left child is RED - hence, n is BLACK

prune

replace_node

grandparent

predecessor

input node, when this predecessor is guaranteed to exist.

name: src/index.js
src/insertion/insert.js
insert
description: Walks the tree rooted at A down the only path that satisfies the following property: if at a node C we make a left (resp. right), then B < C (resp. B >= C). Once we hit the end of the path, we can add node B at this position. By the property of the path, the tree rooted at A is still a binary search tree. For our red-black tree, all that is left to do is fix the red-black tree properties in case they have been violated by this insertion. This is fixed by {@link insert_case0}.

unknown.tagValue: {Node} B - The node that has been inserted.

return.description: B - The node that has been inserted.

name: src/insertion/insert_case0.js
insert_case0
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is red.
  - n's children are BLACK

return.description: The root of the modified subtree.

name: src/insertion/insert_case1.js
insert_case1
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is red.
  - n's children are BLACK
  - n is not the root of the tree.

return.description: The root of the modified subtree.

name: src/insertion/insert_case2.js
insert_case2
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is red.
  - n's children are BLACK
  - n is not the root of the tree.
  - n's parent is red.

return.description: The root of the modified subtree.

name: src/insertion/insert_case3.js
insert_case3
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is red.
  - n's children are BLACK
  - n is not the root of the tree.
  - n's parent is red.
  - n's uncle is black.

Here we fix the input subtree to pass the preconditions of {@link insert_case4}.

return.description: The root of the modified subtree.

name: src/insertion/insert_case4.js
insert_case4
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is red.
  - n's children are BLACK
  - n is not the root of the tree.
  - n's parent is red.
  - n's uncle is black.
  - the path from n to its grandparent makes a left-left or right-right.

return.description: The root of the modified subtree.

name: src/rotate/rotate_left.js
rotate_left
description:
Rotate tree left. (see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree_rotation)

        p                p
        |                |
        A                B
       / \              / \
      x   B     ->     A   y
         / \          / \
        b   y        x   b

name: src/rotate/rotate_right.js
rotate_right
description:
Rotate tree right. (see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree_rotation)

        p                p
        |                |
        B                A
       / \              / \
      A   y     ->     x   B
     / \                  / \
    x   b                b   j

name: src/search/search.js
search
description: Search for the first node whose key equals key.

params.name: root
params.description: The root of the tree to scan.

name: src/swap/swap_color.js
swap_color
description:
Swap colors of two arbitrary nodes.

       -A        +B      ->      +A        -B

name: src/swap/swap_left.js
swap_left
description:
Swap pointers and colors of a node and its left child B with one constraint:
  - B's right child is a leaf

NOTE: This constraint is implied because B is A's in-subtree predecessor.

        p                   p
        |                   |
       -A                  -B
       / \                 / \
     +B   c       ->     +A   c
     / \                 / \
    a   -               a   -

name: src/swap/swap_non_adjacent.js
swap_non_adjacent
description:
Swap pointers and colors of two NON-ADJACENT nodes with three constraints:
  - B is not the root
  - B is its parent right child
  - B's right child is a leaf

NOTE: These three constraints are implied because B is A's in-subtree
predecessor without being A's left child.

        p       q             q           p
        |        \             \          |
       -A        +B            +A        -B
       / \       / \           / \       / \
      u   v     x   -     ->  x   -     u   v

name: src/traversal/inordertraversal.js
inordertraversal
description: Traverses the tree rooted at node in order.

name: src/traversal/leftOpenRangeTraversal.js
leftOpenRangeTraversal
description: Yields all the keys in the tree rooted at root that lie in the interval (-oo, right[, in order.

params.name: right
params.description: The non-inclusive upper bound of the interval.

name: src/traversal/rangetraversal.js
rangetraversal
description: Yields all the keys in the tree rooted at root that lie in the interval [left, right[, in order.

params.name: left
params.description: The inclusive lower bound of the interval.

params.name: right
params.description: The non-inclusive upper bound of the interval.

name: src/traversal/rightOpenRangeTraversal.js
rightOpenRangeTraversal
description: Yields all the keys in the tree rooted at root that lie in the interval [left, +oo), in order.

params.name: left
params.description: The inclusive lower bound of the interval.

name: src/types/Node.js
Node
description: An internal node. This node can be red or black.

name: src/types/RedBlackTree.js
RedBlackTree
description: A RedBlackTree with key-only nodes.

name: constructor
description: Constructs a new empty red-black tree.

params.name: compare
params.description: The comparison function for node keys.

name: isEmpty
description: Tells whether the tree is empty.

name: add
description: Adds a key to the tree.

name: _search
description: Search for the input key in the tree. Returns the first node whose key equals the input key. If no such node exists, returns null.

name: get
description: Search for the input key in the tree. Returns the first node key found in this way (with {@link RedBlackTree#_search}. If no such key exists in the tree, returns null.

name: has
description: Returns true if and only if the tree contains the input key.

name: unlink
description: Deletes the input node from the tree.

name: remove
description: Search for the first node of the tree whose key equals the input key (with {@link RedBlackTree#_search}), then delete that node (with {@link RedBlackTree#unlink}). If such a node is found and deleted then return true. Return false otherwise.

unknown.tagValue: {boolean} - Whether the key existed in the tree before removal.

return.description: Whether the key existed in the tree before removal.

name: range
description:
Returns an in order iterator over the keys of the tree that lie in the
interval [left, right[.

params.name: left
params.description: The left bound of the interval.

params.name: right
params.description: The right bound of the interval.

name: items
description: Returns an in order iterator over the keys of the tree.

name: [Symbol.iterator]
description: Same as {@link RedBlackTree#items}.

name: empty
description: Constructs an empty red-black tree.

name: from
description: Constructs a red-black tree from an input iterable.

content:
# Installation
Can be managed using
[jspm](http://jspm.io)
or [npm](https://github.com/npm/npm).

### jspm
```terminal
jspm install npm:@aureooms/js-red-black-tree
```

### npm
```terminal
npm install @aureooms/js-red-black-tree --save
```
